 to analyze the ways in which Guiding sought to mold young people in England, Canada, and India. She weaves together a fascinating account that connects the histories of girlhood, internationalism, and empire, while asking how girls and young women understood and responded to Guiding’s attempts to lead them toward a service-oriented, “useful” feminine future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aGirl GuideszCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 0aGirl GuideszEnglandxHistoryy20th century. 0aGirl GuideszIndiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aGirlszCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 0aGirlszCanaday20th century. 0aGirlszEnglandxHistoryy20th century. 0aGirlszEnglandy20th century. 0aGirlszIndiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aGirlszIndiay20th century. 7aHISTORY / Women .2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311127365508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2017z978311127619908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311141793640uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077483589340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774835893423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774835893/original  a978-3-11-127365-5  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-127619-9  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-141793-6  University of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles